title: Michigan extends May, ending Indiana speculation
description: Michigan men's basketball coach Dusty May has agreed to a new multiyear agreement with the school, athletic director Warde Manuel announced Friday, effectively removing May from consideration for the vacancy at Indiana.
author: Jeff Borzello

title: Jaguars name Rams exec Gladstone new GM
description: The Jaguars have hired former Rams personnel executive James Gladstone as the team's new general manager, the team announced Friday.
author: Michael Dirocco

title: 'England to monster Scotland? Where's the evidence?'
description: All the Calcutta Cup talk is of England ending Scotland's dominance, but it would be foolish to write off the visitors, writes Tom English.

title: Lionesses have 'lots to work on' but Wiegman 'not concerned'
description: Is there reason to be concerned by the Lionesses' form or is there enough to suggest England are on the right path?

title: Cooper Flagg's prep team a 'modern-day Fab Five' had it stuck together
description: Last year's Montverde Academy team may be one of the best prep teams ever. Could it have made an NCAA tourney run if the players went to the same college?
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Al Michaels recalls iconic call on 45th anniversary of 'Miracle on Ice': 'Nothing will ever beat that'
description: USA's upset of the Soviet Union at the 1980 Olympics was only the second hockey game Michaels had ever called.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Parker at career heaviest as Bakole makes epic journey to Riyadh
description: Joseph Parker weighed in at the heaviest weight of his career for Saturday's heavyweight collision, even as new opponent Martin Bakole was still travelling out for the fight.

title: Warren: Dubois could rematch AJ next, or fight Usyk for undisputed title
description: Daniel Dubois missed out on a world title defence when illness prevented him from boxing Joseph Parker, with promoter Frank Warren now looking at alternative fights.
